The '''Anti-Corruption Commission of Myanmar''' ({{lang-my|အဂတိလိုက်စားမှု တိုက်ဖျက်ရေး ကော်မရှင်}}; abbreviated '''ACC''') is a 15-member body responsible for investigating [[Corruption in Myanmar|corruption allegations in the country]].<ref name="tm">{{cite news|url=http://www.mmtimes.com/index.php/national-news/10636-graft-scandal-sinks-without-trace.html|title=Graft scandal sinks without trace|last=Tim McLaughlin|author2=Aung Shin|date=9 June 2014|work=Myanmar Times|accessdate=17 July 2015}}</ref> It was formed under the 2013 Anti-Corruption Law, which was enacted in September 2013.<ref name="tm"/> Most of the appointed members are former high-ranking military personnel.<ref name="nkk">{{cite news|url=http://www.mmtimes.com/index.php/national-news/11440-anti-corruption-commission-needs-reform.html|title=Anti-Corruption Commission needs reform|last=Naing Ko Ko |date=25 August 2014|work=Myanmar Times|accessdate=17 July 2015}}</ref> The commission was formed on 25 February, 2014.<ref name="eetl">{{cite news|url=http://www.mmtimes.com/index.php/national-news/9746-doubts-emerge-over-anti-graft-commission.html|title=Doubts emerge over anti-graft commission|last=Ei Ei Toe Lwin|date=3 March 2014|work=Myanmar Times|accessdate=17 July 2015}}</ref>
