{{Political corruption sidebar|image=[[File:Flag of Senegal.svg|150 px]]}}
President [[Macky Sall]] has taken some significant efforts to combat corruption in [[Senegal]], including the establishment of several anti-corruption agencies, such as the Ministry of the Promotion of Good Governance and the reactivated Court of Repression of Economic and Financial Crime. The prosecution of corruption committed by officials has also increased under Sall's administration.<ref>{{cite web|title=Senegal Corruption Profile |url=http://www.business-anti-corruption.com/country-profiles/sub-saharan-africa/senegal/show-all.aspx|publisher=Business Anti-Corruption Portal|accessdate=14 July 2015}}</ref>

The investigation into former President [[Abdoulaye Wade]] and his administration continues in 2014 after being charged for massive embezzlement and misuse of public funds.<ref>{{cite web|title=Business Corruption in Senegal|url=http://www.business-anti-corruption.com/country-profiles/sub-saharan-africa/senegal/show-all.aspx|publisher=Business Anti-Corruption Portal|accessdate=14 July 2015}}</ref> Corruption is common among low-level officials and petty corruption is a fact of daily life.<ref>{{cite web|title=BTI 2014 {{!}} Senegal Country Report|url=http://www.bti-project.org/reports/country-reports/wca/sen/index.nc?tx_itaoreport_pi1[action]=show|publisher=The Bertelsmann Foundation|accessdate=27 March 2014}}</ref>

