{{Infobox criminal | honorific_prefix = | name = Ruben Cavazos | honorific_suffix = | native_name = | native_name_lang = | image = | image_upright = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1956|12|28}} | birth_place = [[United States]] | disappeared_date = | disappeared_place = | disappeared_status = | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | body_discovered = | resting_place = | resting_place_coordinates = | monuments = | residence = | nationality = [[Americans|American]] | other_names = | ethnicity = | citizenship = United States | education = | alma_mater = | occupation = Criminal, writer | years_active = | employer = | organization = [[Mongols (motorcycle club)|Mongols Motorcycle Club]] | agent = | known_for = Former President of Mongols Motorcycle Club | notable_works = | style = | home_town = | salary = | net_worth = | height = | weight = | television = | title = | term = | predecessor = | successor = | party = | movement = | opponents = | boards = | religion = | denomination = | criminal_charge = [[Racketeering]] | conviction_penalty = 14 years | conviction_status = Incarcerated | spouse = <!-- Do not include unless notable or relevant to the crime involved --> | children = <!-- (as above) --> | parents = <!-- (as above) --> | relatives = | callsign = | awards = | website = | allegiance = <!-- [[Lucchese crime family]] (only?) --> | motive = | conviction = | reward_amount = | capture_status = | wanted_by = | partners = | wanted_since = | time_at_large = | escaped = | escape_end = | comments = | victims = | date = | time = | beginyear = | endyear = | country = | states = | locations = | targets = | fatalities = | injuries = | weapons = | apprehended = | imprisoned = | module = | signature = | signature_size = | signature_alt = | footnotes = }}
'''Ruben "Doc" Cavazos''' (born December 28, 1956) is an [[United States|American]] criminal, and former International President of the [[Mongols (motorcycle club)|Mongols Motorcycle Club]]. His autobiography, ''Honor Few, Fear None: The Life & Times of a Mongol'', was published by [[HarperCollins]] in June 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sgvtribune.com/ci_10801614 |title=Police Knew of Mongols in Suburbs |publisher=Sgvtribune.com |date=2010-01-22 |accessdate=2011-10-09}}</ref>
Cavazos was raised by his father in [[Highland Park, Los Angeles, California]] and joined the [[The Avenues (gang)|Avenues]], a [[Mexican American]] [[Gang|street gang]], at an early age before serving time in county jail.<ref>{{cite web|title=United States District Court|website=Mnginteractive.com|url=http://extras.mnginteractive.com/live/media/site205/2009/0707/20090707_022007_cavazos.pdf}}</ref> He has a license to work as a radiology technician, hence the nickname "Doc".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://search.barnesandnoble.com/Honor-Few-Fear-None/Ruben-Cavazos/e/9780061137891/?itm=1 |title=Honor Few, Fear None: The Life and Times of a Mongol |publisher=Search.barnesandnoble.com |date= |accessdate=2011-10-09}}</ref> He later became a member of the Mongols and is one of the gang's most infamous members. He has been blamed for turning the club into one of the largest [[criminal organization]]s on the [[West Coast of the United States]] during his time as President. In order to bolster the club's ranks, he also recruited members of street gangs into the club, much to the disgust of the old school bikers.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mlCf3loTfPQ |title=Bikers Lay Blame As Club Falls |publisher=YouTube |date= |accessdate=2011-10-09}}</ref> He was voted out of the club on August 30, 2008, during a meeting in [[Vernon, California]], due to the majority of the membership believing that he was stealing from the club and provoking a war with the [[Mexican Mafia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.agingrebel.com/?p=435 |title=Will Doc Cavazos Flip? |publisher=Agingrebel.com |date=2008-10-23 |accessdate=2011-10-09}}</ref>
On 30 August, 2008 he was voted out of the Mongols Motorcycle Club, along with his brother and son.<ref>[http://www.onepercenterbikers.com/ruben-doc-cavazos/ Ruben "Doc" Cavazos] from [http://www.OnePercenterBikers.com One Percenter Bikers].</ref>
On October 21, 2008, Cavazos and 37 other Mongols were arrested by the [[Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, Firearms and Explosives]] after an investigation into the club, known as [[Operation Black Rain]]. Police raided his {{convert|2760|sqft|m2|adj=on}} home in [[South Hills (California)|South Hills]], [[West Covina, California]], where he lived with his son, Ruben "Lil Rubes" Cavazos Jr, and brother, Al "the Suit" Cavazos, and seized firearms and bulletproof vests. After his arrest during the Operation Black Rain, he pleaded guilty to the [[racketeering]] charge. He has been sentenced to 14 years in prison.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ruben Cavazos|website=Biography.com|url=http://www.biography.com/people/ruben-cavazos-21241549#president-of-the-mongols-motorcycle-club}}</ref>
