{{Infobox language | name = Temoq | ethnicity = Temoq | speakers = unknown <!--no speaker numbers in the Ethnologue18--> | states = [[Malaysia]] | region = [[Peninsular Malaysia|Malaya]] | familycolor = Austroasiatic | fam2 = [[Aslian languages|Aslian]] | fam3 = [[Southern Aslian languages|Southern]] | iso3 = tmo | glotto = temo1243 | glottorefname = Temoq }}
'''Temoq''' is a severely endangered [[Austroasiatic languages|Austroasiatic language]] spoken in the state of Pahang in [[Peninsular Malaysia|the Malay Peninsula]]. Temoq belongs to the [[Southern Aslian languages|Southern]] branch of the [[Aslian languages]], along with [[Semelai language|Semelai]], [[Semaq Beri language|Semaq Beri]], and [[Mah Meri language|Mah Meri]].
